<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT AXLES: INTERNATIONAL BY SPICER I-BEAM - MAXIMUM LIMITS FOR FRONT AXLE KING PIN - MEASURING SPINDLE
        VERTICAL END PLAY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="measure" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MEASURING SPINDLE VERTICAL END PLAY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block rear wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Raise and support the axle.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the wheel and tire (spindle only if wheel is removed) so that all clearance is taken up
                between the steering knuckle and the axle king pin boss.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a feeler gauge, measure clearance (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200405">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200405" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200405" filename="../figg02/G0200405.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Spindle Vertical End Play Check</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FEELER GAUGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. JACK</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <para>If more than .060 inch (1.524 mm) is measured, add shims as needed to reduce clearance to .005 - .015 inch
            (.1270 - .3810 mm).
        </para>
    </svcproc>
